The 12 Months of (Rare, Unreleased) OK Go came to its riveting conclusion last month and, when it was done, we realized that we had what more or less amounts of a new (but mostly old) OK Go album. If youÃ¢â‚¬â„¢re not already up to speed on your downloads, we encourage you to grab it as one condensed .zip file.

Of course, a lot of the fun was hearing what the band members remembered about these rare songs. So, stored below for posterity, are their comments, now the de facto liner notes for the accidental album. Feel free to lay them out, print them, and paste them over an old LP cover for a vintage record listening experience.
